2011-05-06T05:48:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/taiwan-stock-apacer-technology-china-airlines-eva-airways.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:57 a.m. in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 41.38, or 0.5 percent, to 8,977.23.  Airlines:  EVA Airways Corp. (2618)  (2618 TT) surged 5.5 percent to
NT$28.70.  China Airlines Ltd. (2610)  (2610 TT) gained 3.9 percent to
NT$18.90. Taiwan carriers rose on speculation fuel costs will
fall after oil dropped below $100 a barrel yesterday, said Marc
Wong, an analyst at KGI Securities Co.  Oil prices  are down 12 percent this week. Crude futures in
New York had the biggest one-day decline since April 2009
yesterday.  Apacer Technology Inc. (8271)  (8271 TT) fell 1.2 percent to NT$24,
the most since April 25, after sales dropped 28 percent last
month to NT$767 million ($27 million) from a year earlier.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 